\par \pard\plain \s35\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Operator}
\par \pard\plain \s36\li567\ri0\lin567\rin0\fi0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
An operator is a short notation or syntax pattern for some common routines}{
{\*\atnid }{\*\atnauthor }\chatn{\*\annotation{\*\atndate 1736006903}\ltrpar\rtlch \ltrch\loch{\langfe1023\alang1023\dbch\af11\dbch\af11\lang1023
(e.g., <code>Number a + Number b</code> in place of <code>add(Number a, Number b)</code>, or <code>if true; then say 'Hello, World!'; else die</code> in place of <code>if(true, ()\{say 'Hello, World!'\}, ()\{die\})</code>)}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
. }
\par \pard\plain \s35\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Identifier}
\par \pard\plain \s36\li567\ri0\lin567\rin0\fi0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
